TITLE: Top Cuomo aide's father lobbied the governor's office earlier this year as probes were ongoing
SUMMARY: A firm run by the father of Gov. Andrew Cuomo's closest advisor was actively lobbying members of the governor's team earlier this year.

TITLE: 9/11 families ask Biden not to attend memorial events unless he declassifies documents on Saudis
SUMMARY: A group of 9/11 survivors and families asked President Joe Biden to skip memorial events unless he declassifies documents on Saudi Arabia's role in the attacks.

TITLE: Afghan war has entered 'deadlier and more destructive phase,' UN says
SUMMARY: The U.N. special envoy for Afghanistan on Friday said the war in the country has entered a "deadlier and more destructive phase" and questioned the Taliban's commitment to political settlement.

TITLE: 70% of New York voters say Gov. Andrew Cuomo should resign, majority thinks he should be charged with crime
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden and other top Democrats say New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo should resign due to sexual harassment claims. He also faces potential impeachment.

TITLE: Biden skips victory lap after strong July jobs report, warns of economic peril from rising Covid cases
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden said the strong July jobs numbers were no cause for celebration, because rising Covid cases pose an urgent threat.

TITLE: Biden could start reshaping the Fed next month â€” and progressives will want a say
SUMMARY: The future of the Fed is up for grabs with Wall Street pushing Biden to reappoint Chair Jerome Powell and progressives calling for a fresh face.

TITLE: Unemployment rate falls for every group but is higher for Black and Hispanic workers
SUMMARY: Black and Hispanic unemployment dropped in the July jobs report, but the figures are high compared with the jobless rate for whites and Asians.

TITLE: California shuts down major hydroelectric plant amid record-low water levels at Lake Oroville
SUMMARY: The loss of power could fuel rolling blackouts as the state struggles with a historic drought and record-breaking heat waves.

TITLE: Cuomo impeachment probe nears end, governor agrees to give evidence to investigators
SUMMARY: Lawmakers warned New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo, who is accused of sexual harassment, that their impeachment probe was nearing its end.

TITLE: Biden blocks removal of most Hong Kong residents from U.S. for 18 months, cites China repression
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden said China undermined the rights and freedoms of Hong Kong residents by imposing a security law that has led to arrests there.

TITLE: Richard Trumka, head of AFL-CIO union federation, dies at 72
SUMMARY: Richard Trumka served as president of the 12.5-million-member AFL-CIO since 2009. President Joe Biden called the labor leader a close friend.

TITLE: Infrastructure bill would add $256 billion to deficits over a decade, CBO says
SUMMARY: Senators were waiting on the CBO score as they wrap up amendment votes and the infrastructure bill moves toward final passage.

TITLE: Joe Manchin 'deeply concerned' about Fed's easy-money policy, urges Powell to taper
SUMMARY: Sen. Joe Manchin said Thursday that he is "deeply concerned" about the Fed's stimulus and urged the central bank to taper.

TITLE: Justice Department investigating Phoenix police practices, including use of deadly force, in civil rights probe
SUMMARY: The probe will look at the use of deadly force by Phoenix officers and whether they engage in discriminatory practices, among other issues.

TITLE: Cuomo allies and advisors are split on whether the governor should fight or resign
Iran's hardline cleric Ebrahim Raisi sworn in as president amid slew of tensions
SUMMARY: Raisi's swearing in follows drone strikes on a tanker in the Gulf that have been blamed on Iran, and a threat of attack from Israel.

TITLE: Pete Buttigieg says he doesn't know why Elon Musk's Tesla wasn't invited to Biden's clean-car showcase
SUMMARY: Elon Musk tweeted overnight, "Yeah, seems odd that Tesla wasn't invited" to Biden's clean-car event at the White House alongside Ford, GM and the UAW.

TITLE: Bipartisan infrastructure bill inches through Senate as Schumer pledges to stay until it passes
SUMMARY: The Senate is voting on amendments to the bipartisan infrastructure plan as Majority Leader Chuck Schumer aims to vote on it this week.

TITLE: Manhattan, Westchester, Nassau DAs ask for evidence from Cuomo sex harassment probe
SUMMARY: Westchester DA Mimi Rocah asked N.Y. AG Letitia James to send her materials related to one of the 11 women who in a report accused Cuomo of sexual harassment.

TITLE: Former Cuomo staffer was witness in sexual harassment probe, won't rule out running for governor
SUMMARY: New York state Sen. Alessandra Biaggi was a witness in the attorney general's investigation into Gov. Andrew Cuomo.

TITLE: Trump lawyers ask judge to block release of tax returns to Congress after Biden DOJ orders IRS to do so
SUMMARY: Trump has fought the release of his income tax returns for years. The Biden Justice Department says the IRS has to give Congress those documents.

TITLE: Pentagon police officer killed in unprovoked knife attack, assailant shot himself
SUMMARY: A Pentagon police officer has died after he was stabbed several times in the neck outside the Pentagon on Tuesday, sources confirmed with NBC News.

TITLE: Mexico sues U.S. gun companies, alleging 'massive damage' that is 'destabilizing' to society
SUMMARY: The Mexican government filed a civil lawsuit against several U.S. gun manufacturers, alleging that they contribute to illegal gun trafficking to Mexico.

TITLE: Biden calls on Cuomo to resign after bombshell sexual harassment report
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden called on Democratic New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo to resign Tuesday, following a report that Cuomo sexually harassed 11 women.

TITLE: Cuomo violated federal, state laws as he sexually harassed multiple women, NY attorney general says
SUMMARY: New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo sexually harassed multiple women who worked for the state and elsewhere, a report by state Attorney General Letitia James says.

TITLE: Albany DA criminally investigating Cuomo, asks 'any victim' of New York governor sexual harassment to contact office
SUMMARY: New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo has denied sexually harassing 11 women whose claims are detailed in a report by the office of Attorney General Letitia James.

TITLE: New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo strongly denies sexual harassment claims
SUMMARY: New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo strongly denied claims in a state Attorney General's report that he sexually harassed 11 women and oversaw a "toxic culture."

TITLE: New York Lt. Gov. Hochul says she believes Cuomo accusers, calls his behavior 'repulsive & unlawful'
SUMMARY: New York Lt. Gov. Kathy Hochul said that a report from the state attorney general's office shows "repulsive & unlawful" behavior by Gov. Andrew Cuomo.

TITLE: Cuomo business allies, donors quiet after blockbuster report on sexual harassment allegations
SUMMARY: Andrew Cuomo's business allies are keeping quiet on the state Attorney General's report detailing claims of sexual harassment.

TITLE: Pelosi among top Democrats calling for NY Gov. Cuomo's resignation
SUMMARY: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi called on New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo to resign following the release of a bombshell sexual harassment report.
